                    <h2>Welcome To Artyunk</h2>
            <p>Artyunk is a creative hub in the heart of Manayunk, on Cresson Street, where artists and 
                art lovers come together to explore, learn, and connect. We are building a space that 
                celebrates creativity in all its forms, from casual 
                sketchers to dedicated makers- to engage with art in a fun, social and supportive environment.
                </p>
            <br><h2>Immediate Offerings</h2><br>
	<h3>Ticketed Art Nights / Social Drawing / Theme Nights</h3><p>Relaxed, interactive evenings where you can draw, socialize, and try something new. Perfect for all skill levels.</p>
	<br><h3>Specialty Workshops</h3><p>Longer, skill-focused sessions designed to deepen your practice and explore new techniques.</p>
	<br><h3>Exhibitions & Open Studio Nights</h3><p>Showcasing local talent and inviting the community into the creative process.</p>
</ul>
<br><h2>Future Offerings</h2><br>
    <h3>Studio Memberships</h3><p>Limited, reserved access for ongoing projects in a shared space enviroment.</p>
    <br><h3>Day Studio Rentals</h3><p>Non-member access to the space for a day of focused, uninterrupted creativity.</p>
    <br><h3>Short Project Blocks</h3><p>1-2 week rentals for special projects or intensive creative bursts.</p><br>
            <h2>About Me</h2><p>I am <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/taylor-cardamone/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Taylor Cardamone</a>, a graphic designer, fine artist and animator. <br>With Artyunk, my goal is to create a welcoming, inspiring environment where we build a thriving creative community.</p>
<br><h2>Location & Accessibility</h2><p>Artyunk is located on Cresson Street in Manayunk. The space will be revealed in late spring / early summer. Please note: the studio is not currently handicap accessible at this time.</p>      
<br><h2>Support Our Vision</h2><p>Want to help bring Artyunk to life? Learn how to support us
 and join a growing community dedicated to creativity, connection, and the joy of making.</p>
